<subSubSection id="9884E89DE684C54306E01A70E22B296E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="5F904001CE202C1FBFADE8602F217FDA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="C031AA6CE2CBFC922FFB46897D413298" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Metopomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metopomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Metopomyza</taxonomicName>
Enderlein, 1936a: 180. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="2659A90849E2B35080FA1E33A62D0FE8" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Agromyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Agromyza flavonota" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flavonota">Agromyza flavonota</taxonomicName>
<bibRefCitation id="2E3EBBD75DD44682FEA8D1D77A732639" author="Haliday, AH" journalOrPublisher="Entomological Magazine (London)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="147 - 180" refId="B96" refString="Haliday, AH, 1833. Catalogue of Diptera occurring about Holywood in Downshire. Entomological Magazine (London) 1: 147 - 180" title="Catalogue of Diptera occurring about Holywood in Downshire." volume="1" year="1833">Haliday 1833</bibRefCitation>
, by monotypy. 
<bibRefCitation id="D233E79FE3EEE26B310E4662225D2CA2" author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher="Agriculture Handbook" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 478" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" refId="B261" refString="Spencer, KA, Steyskal, GC, 1986b. Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U.S.D.A. Agriculture Handbook 638: 1 - 478, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" title="Manual of the Agromyzidae (Diptera) of the United States. U. S. D. A." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/page/51258090" volume="638" year="1986 b">Spencer and Steyskal 1986b</bibRefCitation>
: 161; 
<bibRefCitation id="C22F80405398F505F6D271ACA903C8A6" author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 168" refId="B304" refString="Zlobin, VV, 1995. Review of mining flies of the genus Metopomyza Enderlein (Diptera: Agromyzidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research 6: 143 - 168" title="Review of mining flies of the genus Metopomyza Enderlein (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." volume="6" year="1995">Zlobin 1995</bibRefCitation>
: 143, 
<bibRefCitation id="A86D11A6B47312EDE867C9722F96A184" author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="247 - 251" refId="B311" refString="Zlobin, VV, 2002b. Further new Metopomyza species from the Palaearctic region. An International Journal of Dipterological Research 13 (4): 247 - 251" title="Further new Metopomyza species from the Palaearctic region." volume="13" year="2002 b">2002b</bibRefCitation>
: 247.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C9A5995E445C8EF01E07D4731992D061" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note">
<paragraph id="AFE31E2B2238169BFEE40C9987B1BB57" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="45F6367E5938041F598E62A446152BB3" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Poaceae" genus="Metopomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metopomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B3D52BEDE36DC399F4C77FA3441AF70A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Metopomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, defined and treated in reviews by 
<bibRefCitation id="B2CF80F48980E6FBC220B05589A1957E" author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 168" refId="B304" refString="Zlobin, VV, 1995. Review of mining flies of the genus Metopomyza Enderlein (Diptera: Agromyzidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research 6: 143 - 168" title="Review of mining flies of the genus Metopomyza Enderlein (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." volume="6" year="1995">Zlobin (1995</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="E62A18F54A4D94E33CC709CD33DB645D" author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="247 - 251" refId="B311" refString="Zlobin, VV, 2002b. Further new Metopomyza species from the Palaearctic region. An International Journal of Dipterological Research 13 (4): 247 - 251" title="Further new Metopomyza species from the Palaearctic region." volume="13" year="2002 b">2002b</bibRefCitation>
), is a small Holarctic genus hypothesized to be an ancient offshoot of 
<taxonomicName id="F3B460DC2F1A4EE7670606EE3ADA6D7A" authorityName="Hendel" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Phytoliriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phytoliriomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="13D9ADF8B8A04DF667DB26C7BDE9B1EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Phytoliriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that specialises on monocots (
<bibRefCitation id="4BBEB29B3A62C8F63506E77119A16498" author="Spencer, KA" journalOrPublisher=", Klampenborg, Denmark" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B251" refString="Spencer, KA, 1976. The Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica 5. Scandinavian Science Press, Ltd., Klampenborg, Denmark" title="The Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Fennoscandia and Denmark. Fauna Entomologica Scandinavica 5. Scandinavian Science Press, Ltd." year="1976">Spencer 1976</bibRefCitation>
a, 1990). The dense arrangement of tubercle-like setae on the epandrium and the morphology of the hypandrial complex would certainly seem to support this notion, but similarities to the Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="5D595186E26F1AAD07ED59F5DACABB19" authorityName="Wahlberg" authorityYear="1844" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Selachops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Selachops" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="256F37C922AC48CA04894073F05DAE4F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Selachops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also numerous and require further examination. 
<taxonomicName id="2ADE7BB1AB4B7A7E4C3675C654CC21C6" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Poaceae" genus="Metopomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metopomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D32EE737B5CDE35952CF5D7F4616513A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Metopomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficially resembles 
<taxonomicName id="9F8535F402DD704B370D0DE97E89392B" authorityName="Mik" authorityYear="1894" class="Insecta" family="Phytomyzinae" genus="Liriomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Liriomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FCAC5DB84496C6205F0181350ADC105A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Liriomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a yellow scutellum (uncommonly entirely dark) and a dark shiny scutum, but the head is darkly pigmented, at least laterally along the fronto-orbital plate, and the fronto-orbital plate is relatively pronounced and well-sclerotised, reaching (or nearly reaching) the lateral corner of the ocellar triangle to form the outline of an 
<normalizedToken id="3834D1281C3BBADFF38265EAA7966399" originalValue="“M”">&quot;M&quot;</normalizedToken>
along the posterior margin of the frons. Internally, the epandrium has two comb-like bands of tubercle-like setae. The posterior larval spiracles have minute spherical bulbs on long stalks (
<bibRefCitation id="D2D4398E4CE166A58770D3763464E1E5" author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 168" refId="B304" refString="Zlobin, VV, 1995. Review of mining flies of the genus Metopomyza Enderlein (Diptera: Agromyzidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research 6: 143 - 168" title="Review of mining flies of the genus Metopomyza Enderlein (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." volume="6" year="1995">Zlobin 1995</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EC04118A3451BA0CF38B5C7514800001" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Six species of 
<taxonomicName id="AA9E1FEE8F4EA603317A2E1089B8036D" authorityName="Enderlein" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Poaceae" genus="Metopomyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Metopomyza" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="199B2185A13E571033C49BFBD33FCDB0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Metopomyza</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are known from the Nearctic. Only 
<taxonomicName id="5A7C87E1C02D193BBA9A85B806C50C4D" family="Asteraceae" genus="M." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="M. interfrontalis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="interfrontalis">
<emphasis id="5718ADE873C8201691A9E1B0702564C7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. interfrontalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Melander) is known from the Delmarva states.
</paragraph>
